# Open Generative AI — Fork maintenance

**Upstream:** https://github.com/Anil-matcha/Open-Generative-AI (branch `main`)
**This fork:** Runware + UI tweaks. **Default cloud provider:** Muapi (never remove).
**Sync runbook:** [`docs/UPSTREAM-SYNC.md`](../../docs/UPSTREAM-SYNC.md)

## Sync policy (user priority)

When upstream and the fork both changed the **same area**: adopt **upstream** if their feature or fix is **better**. Drop or rework fork code in that spot. Re-wire fork-only layers (Runware, routing, dual-provider entry) after accepting upstream studio/catalog changes.

**Decision order:** (1) upstream better → theirs + re-wire hooks; (2) fork-only → ours; (3) unclear → smoke test, document in `FORK.md`.

## Before every change

1. Is this **fork-only**? Put it in dedicated paths (see Tier 1), not scattered edits.
2. Does it touch **high-churn upstream files** (`models.js`, `muapi.js`, `*Studio.jsx`)? Minimize diff; use abstractions.
3. Can you **add** without deleting Muapi behavior? Prefer additive changes.

## Merge conflict tiers

### Tier 1 — Protected (fork-only)

Keep **ours** unless upstream ships the same capability and theirs is better.

| Paths |
|-------|
| `packages/studio/src/providers/**`, `models.runware*.js`, `providerFactory.js`, `modelRegistry.js` |
| `studioCloud.js`, `studioGenerate.js`, `useStudioCloud.js`, `cloudRoutingStore.js`, `cloudKeyStore.js`, `cloudSession.js` |
| `app/api/runware/**` |
| `StandaloneShell.js`, `ApiKeyModal.js`, cloud key/settings UI |
| `.cursor/rules/**`, `FORK.md`, `SECURITY.md`, `SUPPORT.md`, README fork block |
| parity fixtures, fork-only tests/scripts |

### Tier 2 — Prefer upstream

Take **theirs** first; keep fork diff only if smoke test proves fork is better.

| Paths |
|-------|
| `packages/studio/src/models.js` (Runware stays in `models.runware.*`) |
| `packages/studio/src/muapi.js`, `app/api/api/v1/**`, `app/api/agents/**` |
| submodule pointers, `electron/lib/localInference*` |
| new upstream-only studio features |

### Tier 3 — Overlap (upstream wins if better)

| Paths | Rule |
|-------|------|
| `*Studio.jsx` | Start from upstream; port Runware hooks, mentions, Recreate, cost as needed |
| theme / i18n / `src/styles/**` | Prefer upstream UI if better; re-apply fork tokens where needed |
| `README.md` | Upstream body + re-apply fork block |
| `packages/studio/src/index.js` | Upstream exports + fork exports |

Resolve **per file**. Document in `FORK.md` **Merge decisions**.

## Forbidden

- Removing or disabling Muapi as the default cloud path.
- Embedding Runware logic inside `muapi.js` or the Muapi proxy routes.
- Adding Runware models inside the main `models.js` blob.
- Committing API keys, `.env`, or secrets.
- Agent commit/push **without** `npm run security:secrets` (before commit) or `npm run security:secrets:git` (before push).
- `git add -f` on `.env` or secret-bearing files.
- Drive-by formatting or refactors in untouched files.

## After merging upstream

1. `git submodule update --init --recursive`
2. `npm run setup` if workspaces or lockfile changed
3. `npm run check:full-parity`
4. Smoke: Muapi image gen; Runware routing; Agents Muapi-locked
5. Update `FORK.md` **Upstream baseline**, **Last upstream merge**, **Merge decisions**; sync README fork block if README conflicted
6. See [`docs/UPSTREAM-SYNC.md`](../../docs/UPSTREAM-SYNC.md) for full checklist

## Diff discipline

Smallest correct diff. One concern per commit when possible.

## Git operations

Follow [`.cursor/rules/git-secrets-and-push.mdc`](git-secrets-and-push.mdc). The user delegates commit/push to the agent.

- **Conventional Commits** for subjects; update [`FORK.md`](../../FORK.md) **Differences from upstream** and README **This fork** table only when user-visible behavior changes.
- Run gitleaks before commit and push (`security:secrets` / `security:secrets:git`).
